pytest -v pytest_topics
pytest -s ( It will not give any detailed output)
pytest --sw ( It will stop the test at the first occurence of any test failure)
Name all test modules with test_<some_name>.py
Name all test functions with def test_<some_name>():
Test classes should be named Test<somename>.py
def test_a1():
    assert 5+5 == 10, "test passed"
pytest -v pytest_topics\test_module02.py::TestMyStuff
pytest -v -m "sanity"
pytest -v -m "sanity and not str"
pytest -v -m "sanity and str"
pytest -v -k 'module' --tb=no ( trace back error it is not going to show )
pytest --collect-only
pytest --lf ( last fail)
pytest --ff ( failed first)
